🟡 **WARNING** `vize:croquis/cf/provide-without-symbol`

### provide() uses string key

**Problem**: `provide('user')` uses a string key instead of Symbol/InjectionKey.

**Why string keys are problematic**:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  String Keys          │  Symbol/InjectionKey           │
├───────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┤
│  ❌ Name collisions    │  ✅ Guaranteed uniqueness       │
│  ❌ No type safety     │  ✅ Full TypeScript inference   │
│  ❌ Refactoring breaks │  ✅ IDE rename support          │
│  ❌ Hard to trace      │  ✅ Go-to-definition works      │
└───────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Name collision example**:

```ts
// ComponentA.vue
provide('user', myData)

// LibraryX (unknown to you)
provide('user', otherData)  // 💥 Collision!
```

**Type-safe pattern with InjectionKey**:

```ts
// injection-keys.ts
import type { InjectionKey, Ref } from 'vue'

export interface UserState {
  name: string
  id: number
}

export const UserKey: InjectionKey<Ref<UserState>> = Symbol('user')

// Provider.vue
import { UserKey } from './injection-keys'
provide(UserKey, userData)  // ✅ Type-checked

// Consumer.vue
import { UserKey } from './injection-keys'
const user = inject(UserKey)  // ✅ Type: Ref<UserState> | undefined
```
